short_text_with_quiz.text_japanese: 今週、友達と旅行に行く予定です。ずっと行きたかった素敵な場所に行くんです。旅行のために貯金していたのですが、予算が足りなくて諦めることにしました。言えば、先日銀行で両替をしました。両替って、結構面倒ですよね。今回の旅行では、友達と色々な話を交換したいと思っています。
short_text_with_quiz.text_english: This week, I'm planning to go on a trip with my friends.  We are going to a beautiful place that I have been wanting to visit for a long time. We have been saving up for this trip, but we have decided that we won't be able to go because we don't have enough money. Speaking of money, the other day I went to exchange some money at the bank. I have to say that exchanging money can be a hassle at times. I'm looking forward to exchanging stories with my friends on this trip.

reading_comprehension_quiz_in_japanese.question: 次の文の中で、予算という言葉を使った文はどれですか？

options.text: 来週の天気予報は雨だそうです。
今週は予算が足りないため、旅行は諦めることにしました。
来週の会議は、予約制なので、事前に連絡しておきましょう。

song_lyrics.lyrics_japanese: 明日の天気予報は雨だって、だから傘を持っていくよ。そういえば、傘を新しくしないといけないんだ。この傘、古くなってきたから。新しいのを買おうかなってずっと思ってたんだけど、予算がなくて後回しにしてたんだ。でも、もし雨の途中で壊れたら大変だよね。だから明日は新しいのを買おうかな。やっぱり、安全第一だよね。それと、交通安全の新しいキャンペーンが始まるみたい。みんなに気を付けてほしいって言うんだ。事故は簡単に起こるって言うから。私も、地域を安全に守るために気をつけなきゃ。
song_lyrics.lyrics_english_translation: The weather forecast says it's going to rain tomorrow, so I'll bring an umbrella. Speaking of umbrellas, I need to get a new one. This one is getting old. I've been thinking about getting a new one for a while now, but I've been putting it off because of my budget. However, if it were to break in the middle of the rain, it wouldn't be a good situation. So I'll buy a new one tomorrow. It's better to be safe than sorry. There's also a new traffic safety campaign starting. They're asking everyone to be more careful. They say accidents happen very easily. I want to make sure to do my part in keeping our community safe.

kanji_list.image_description: Two whimsical mountains, each topped with a single glowing orb, stand side-by-side within an upside-down box.  The box is filled with tiny cars, all lined up in a single row. The entire scene is bathed in warm, golden light.

A giant, smiling '了' character stands on a pedestal, with a tiny 'マ' character rushing towards it. The '了' character is adorned with a crown and a cape, while the 'マ' character is holding a map and wearing a travel hat.

Two pigs wearing tiny suits,  with their heads stuck out of a giant wrapping enclosure. The enclosure is filled with stacks of gold coins, and the pigs are arguing over them, their tails wagging furiously.

A giant kettle lid, with a smiling father character standing on top.  They are both holding hands, surrounded by swirling clouds of smoke.  The kettle lid is pouring out a colorful stream of people, all coming and going in a chaotic and joyful dance.

A person character, wearing a costume of a giant '也' character, is standing on a stage in front of a huge, vibrant crowd. The '也' character is smiling and waving to the audience, who are all cheering and throwing flowers.  The person character seems surprised and overwhelmed by the attention.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 予算を慎重に検討した上で、プロジェクトの延期を決めた。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: Upon careful consideration of the budget, we decided to postpone the project.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 両替をした上で、買い物に行った。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: After the money exchange, we went shopping.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 交通安全という上で、誰もが注意しなければならない。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: When it comes to traffic safety, everyone must be careful.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 外交という上で、他の国との良好な関係を維持することが重要だ。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: For the sake of diplomacy, it's important to maintain good relations with other countries.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 予約をする上で、電話でご連絡ください。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: In order to make a reservation, please contact us by phone.
